I"]<p>These are summits I recommend for beginners (or just when you want a low-effort activation) in Georgia.</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4ghc-003-stone-mountain">W4G/HC-003 Stone Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Near Atlanta; can ride the tram to the summit.  Technician: should have plenty VHF activity.  Try not to set up in the middle of where people walk.  (Yes, there is a tree up there.)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4ghc-005-springer-mountain">W4G/HC-005, Springer Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Famous start of Appalachian Trail; easy to follow trail.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4ghc-036-pine-mountain">W4G/HC-036 Pine Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>All paved-road drive; view; near Atlanta; near I-75; Technician: should have plenty VHF activity.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4ghc-043-vineyard-mountain">W4G/HC-043 Vineyard Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Near Atlanta.  Technician: should have plenty VHF activity.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4gng-001-brasstown-bald">W4G/NG-001 Brasstown Bald</a>
    <ul>
      <li>All paved-road drive; summit is accessible for limited-mobility hams; highest point in Georgia; restrooms at the summit; view.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4gng-020-wildcat-mountain">W4G/NG-020, Wildcat Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>All paved-road drive; less than a mile hike; view.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4gng-024-black-mountain">W4G/NG-022, Black Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Easy to follow trail; all paved-road drive.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><a href="/content/sota-guide-w4gng-027-black-rock-mountain">W4G/NG-027, Black Rock Mountain</a>
    <ul>
      <li>Less than a mile hike; all paved-road drive; view.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
:ET